For National Eat Outside Day, take a break and get out of the library! 

There are great places to eat a snack or your lunch outdoors around the Health Science Center, including the patio on the second floor of the Communicore, the tables outside the Harrell Medical Education Building, or the picnic pavilion in the Bartram-Carr Park.    

So get outside and explore!
Health Science Center Library puzzling gets personnel!
UF Health Science Center Libraries updated their address.

Come to the library to … take a nap! Conveniently located on the 2nd floor of the HSC Library, our new energy pods allow you to take a much needed break from studying, kick back, and put your feet up. The pods play soothing music and provide privacy while you snooze. But don’t worry, the automatic timer won’t let you oversleep and miss class.
Loud roommate? Stay with us! Individual and group study rooms are waiting for you at the HSC Library. All you need is a Gator 1 ID. Ask us for a key at the 1st floor Information Desk.
HSC librarian demonstrates how to use a pinhole camera- and it actually works... and with two piecesof card, or with leaves...

Staggering under the weight of those brand new textbooks? Take a load off your back! Lockers are available on the second floor of the Communicore building.  Reserve your locker at the HSC Library Information Desk for either the full semester or just for the day.

Remember: our FREE comic-creation workshop is TOMORROW from 6-9pm at the Sequential Artist Workshop on 710 SE 2nd Street, across from Depot Park & Rosa Parks bus station! 

Come learn how to use comics and graphic novel art to create a healthier community!  

Learn more: http://guides.uflib.ufl.edu/graphic-novel-contest

Learn more about creating visual narratives that address community health concerns and making a positive difference in the community through published works!

This Tuesday, June 13th, from 6-9pm,  come join others interested in using comics and art to promote health, and learn about the process of creating graphic novels from renowned Sequential Artists Workshop faculty.  Health science librarians will also present on finding HIV/AIDS information online to use in graphic novels.  The workshop is free and open to the public – all skill levels welcome!

What: Graphic Novel Creation Workshop
When: Tuesday, June 13th, 6-9pm
Where: New Sequential Artists Workshop Building, 710 SE 2nd St, Gainesville, FL 32601

This workshop is part of an HIV/AIDS graphic novel contest hosted by the UF Health Science Center Libraries, in collaboration with the Sequential Artists Workshop.  Learn more about the contest here: http://guides.uflib.ufl.edu/graphic-novel-contest.
Looking to escape the heat (or, in the afternoon, torrential rains)?  Chill in the HSC Library and work on our latest puzzle!

Attention all artists, health promoters, and those interested in making a difference in their community!  

The HSCL is hosting a graphic novel contest this summer to promote HIV/AIDS education resources, like AIDSource (https://aids.nlm.nih.gov/).  We'll be taking the top submissions and publishing them in a collection that will be shared throughout Gainesville & Jacksonville!  If you're interested in medicine, public health, or just helping your friends and neighbors make healthy choices, check out the contest guidlines here: https://goo.gl/fQ2km5.
